    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="CH2a1370-start">
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T19:01:01.815+09:00">it's always been that way.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T19:01:55.387+09:00">The relation between Fu Yi [d. 90' and Ban Gu [32-92]</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T19:13:04.236+09:00">Yet Ban Gu belittled him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T19:13:53.326+09:00">writing in a letter to his elder brother Ban Zhao [33-108]:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T19:28:04.938+09:00">was nothing less than the relation of a younger brother to an elder brother.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T20:22:39.148+09:00">Wuzhong [Fu Yi] became Imperial Librarian through his facility in composition</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T20:33:20.038+09:00">whenever he used his writing brush, he couldn't stop himself."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T20:34:12.918+09:00">People are good at [or fond of] making themselves known;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T20:34:42.769+09:00">but since literature (wen*) is not of one form alone</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T20:45:10.294+09:00">few can be good at everything.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T20:56:35.696+09:00">Thus by the criterion of those things in which he is strong</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:01:45.31+09:00">The is a village saying:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:02:08.88+09:00">"The worn-out broom that belongs to my own household</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:02:20.361+09:00">is worth a thousand in gold."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:02:33.048+09:00">Such is the ill consequence of a lack of self-awareness.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:04:10.446+09:00">A superior person examines himself to measure others;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:04:43.323+09:00">and thus he is able to avoid such entanglements [e.g., envy and blindness to the worth of others.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:04:54.71+09:00">Thus I have written a discourse on literature.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:05:21.473+09:00">Wang Can excels in poetic expositions;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:05:42.037+09:00">Even though Xu Gan at times shows languid qi,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:05:49.567+09:00">still he is Wang Can's match.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:07:21.561+09:00">Works like Wang Can's "Beginning of the Journey," "Climbing a Tower," "The Locust Tree," or "Thoughts on Travel";</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:08:08.356+09:00">or works like Xu Gan's "The Black Gibbon," "The Syphon," "The Circular Fan," or "The Orange Tree",</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:08:50.734+09:00">even Zhang Heng [78-139] and Cai Yong [132-192] do not surpass.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:11:09.434+09:00">Yet their other writings</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:11:09.841+09:00">In regard to memorials, letters, and records, those of Chen Lin and Ruan Yu</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:11:10.452+09:00">are preeminent in the present.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:11:09.683+09:00">are no match for these.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:11:30.383+09:00">Ying Chang is agreeable but lacks vigor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.51" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:12:02.704+09:00">Liu Chen is vigorous but holds nothing concealed [mi; i.e., in reserve].</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.52" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:12:18.984+09:00">Kong Rong's form and qi are lofty and subtle,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:12:33.306+09:00">with something in them that surpasses all the others;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.54" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:12:57.3+09:00">but he cannot sustain an argument,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.55" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:13:14.502+09:00">and the principle in his work is not up to the diction,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.56" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:13:32.027+09:00">to the point that he mixes his writing with playfulness and spoofing.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.57" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:13:39.753+09:00">At his best</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.58" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:14:34.64+09:00">he rivals Yang Xiong [53 B.C. - A.D. 18] and Ban Gu.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.59" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:15:10.661+09:00">Ordinary people value what is far away and feel contempt for what is close at hand.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.60" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:37.087+09:00">The favor repute and turn their backs on substance.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.61" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:37.328+09:00">Moreover, they suffer the ill consequences of ignorance in self-awareness,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.62" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:37.705+09:00">claiming to be men of great worth.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.63" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:37.58+09:00">Literature</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.64" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:38.08+09:00">is the same at the root, but differs in its branches [mo, a 'branch tip," the later stages of a process.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.65" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:37.512+09:00">Generally speaking, memorials and disquisitions should have dignity;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.66" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:37.705+09:00">letters and memorials should be based on natural principle;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.67" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:37.923+09:00">inscriptions and eulogy value the facts;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.68" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:38.162+09:00">poetry and poetic exposition aspire to beauty.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.69" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:38.352+09:00">Each of these four categories is different,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.70" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:38.558+09:00">so that  a writer's ability will favor some over others.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.71" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:38.755+09:00">Only a comprehensive talent can achieve the full complement of these forms.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.72" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:38.95+09:00">In literature qi is the dominant factor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.73" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:20:39.548+09:00">Qi has its normative forms -clear and murky.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.74" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:21:04.284+09:00">It is not to be brought by force.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.75" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:21:11.842+09:00">Compare it to music:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.76" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:21:31.465+09:00">though melodies can be equal</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.77" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:21:49.16+09:00">and though the rhythms follow the rules,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.78" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:22:04.995+09:00">when it comes to an inequlity in drawing on a reserve of qi,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.79" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:22:19.971+09:00">we have grounds to distinguish skill and clumsiness.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.80" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:22:35.443+09:00">Althought it may reside in a father</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.81" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:23:12.721+09:00">he cannot transfer it to his son; nor can an elder brother transfer it to a younger.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.82" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:24:20.779+09:00">I would say that literary works are the supreme achievement in the business of the state,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.83" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:24:27.164+09:00">a splendor that does not decay.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.84" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:24:37.665+09:00">A time will come when a person's life ends;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.85" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:24:52.3+09:00">glory and pleasure go no futher than this body.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.86" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:25:02.031+09:00">To carry both to eternity,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.87" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:10.63+09:00">there is nothing to compare with the unending permanence of the literary work.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.88" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:10.873+09:00">So writers of ancient times</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.89" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:10.92+09:00">entrusted their persons to ink and the brush,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.90" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:11.038+09:00">and let their thoughts be seen in their composition;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.91" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:11.263+09:00">depending neither on a good historian</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.92" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:11.068+09:00">nor on a momentum from a powerful patron,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.93" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:11.265+09:00">their reputations were handed down to posterity on their own force.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.94" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:11.479+09:00">The Earl of the West [later made King Wen of the Zhou], when imprisoned, amplified the Book of Changes;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.95" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:11.68+09:00">the Duke of Zhou, though in his glory, prescribed the Rites.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.96" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:11.904+09:00">The former did not ignore this [the importance of literary work] in spite of hardship;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.97" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:12.102+09:00">the latter was not distracted by health and pleasure.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.98" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:12.322+09:00">From this we can see</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.99" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:12.546+09:00">how the ancients thought nothing of large jade disks [marks of wealth], but valued each moment,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.100" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:12.815+09:00">fearful lest their time pass them by.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.101" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:31:13.314+09:00">Yet people usually do not extert themselves:</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.102" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:32:52.909+09:00">in poverty and low station they fear the hunger and cold;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.103" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:33:15.36+09:00">amid wealth and honor they drift with the distractions of pleasure.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.104" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:33:38.506+09:00">They busy themselves with the demands of what lies right before their eyes,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.105" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:33:53.05+09:00">and neglect an accomplishment lasting a thousand years.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.106" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:34:09.486+09:00">Overhead, the days and months pass away form us;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.107" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:34:26.001+09:00">here below, face and body waste away.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.108" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:34:59.692+09:00">Suddenlywe will move off into transformations with all the other things of the world -</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.109" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:35:12.548+09:00">this is the greatest pain for a person with high aspirations.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#CH2a1370_CHANT_001-1a.110" xml:lang="en" resp="CH" modified="2020-02-14T22:35:29.592+09:00">Kong Rong and the others have already passed away,</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
